captions.text: -Hey, everyone.

I'm Mindy from Cute
Girls Hairstyles.

Today I'm going to show
you a DIY hairstyle that's
really fast and very cute.

Now, this hairstyle is
designed to be a little more

messy, a little
more romantic feel

to it, a little looser, which
is why it's a great one for when

you're on day three
with your hair,

or you're in a real
hurry in the morning

and you need to be able
to do it really fast.

But before we move
on to the hair,

just very quickly wanted
to remind everyone,

this is the last week to
enter our 500,000th Subscriber
Giveaway.

So for those of you that
missed it on Wednesday,

we uploaded a huge
giveaway video,

and it ends this coming
Saturday, November 24,
at midnight.

And on the 25th, which
is a week from today,

we will be announcing
the 16 winners.

So make sure you check out the
video if you haven't seen it,
and continue to enter all week.

And then watch video
next week to find out
who all the winners are.

Don't forget, also, that we
announced our limited edition

Cute Girls Hairstyle
T-shirts in that video.

If you are interested in one,
you can click the link below.

I'll have it in the
description box.

OK, we're calling this hairstyle
Subtle Twist Into Side Braid.

So as you can see,
I just have my hair

like I normally wear
it on most days.

It's been a couple
days since I've

washed it, which is a great
reason to use this hairstyle.

So I'm going to
just take my bangs,

and I'm going to flip them
all to the right side,

just because I want
all of my bangs
into the twist on this one.

And I'm literally not even
going to use a brush, just
my fingers.

I'm going to take the first
little piece right here

and divide it in half, because
we're creating a twist.

And I'm going to
start the twist,

always going back
away from my forehead.

I'm going to pick up a little
hair, twist it again over here
that back strand.
Pick up a little hair.
Twist it over the back strand.

And this is just a
way to kind of get

my bangs twisted into it,
so that they don't fall out.
OK?

Now you can go back and
loosen this up a little,

so it's really soft and
subtle, which I like.

Now, when you get
to this part-- you

can see that I don't
have enough hair

to twist all the
way down the strand.

So now I'm going to
take a bigger piece

and add into that front twist,
and do it one more time.

So did you see how I got a
lot more length right there?

We're going to need that
to continue on the twist.

OK, so now that I have
length in both pieces,

I'm just going to twist
them over each other.
Don't worry if that happens.
Not a big deal.

Remember, it's all about
the loose, the messy,
the romance in the hair.
So not a big deal.

You can use a clip or
anything you want, an elastic

at this point, to
just secure this end.

If I wasn't talking
to the camera,

I'd stick the hair in my teeth
and hold it with my teeth.

But I won't, since I'm
talking to you guys.
OK.

So now that you have your twist,
take the rest of your hair,

sweet it very gently
over to that same side.

I'm going to turn a little
more so you can see.
Doesn't have to be pretty.
Doesn't have to be really fancy.

Once you've got the
hair, minus the twist--
I'm gonna hold in my teeth.

Then separate out this
into three sections.

Now, I'm going to
take this and put it
into this middle section.

You can do it on
whichever one you want.
And then begin just to braid.
How easy is this?

And then, of course, I'm going
to have to remove that elastic,
now that my braid is going.

Make sure you pick
up any strays.

So we're just doing
a nice side braid.

When you get to where your
hair is starting to fall out,
use another elastic to secure.

OK, now this too structured
for me, for this look.
So now I'm going to mess it up.

So I'm going to go in
here, maybe right here.

I'm going to pull some loosies
out and let them be softer.

And maybe some right
here by my ears, just

some really soft, natural--
and what you'll find

is this'll kind of
naturally happen

as you go through
the day anyway.

Just as you're moving around
and running around and stuff,

your hair kind of
naturally loosens up.

I'm going to take the
braid, fluff it a little.
Pull it.
Just make it messy.

The twist, we're just
going to leave it soft.
And there you go.
How easy was that?

Thank you to the girl at Target
that I saw with this hairdo
on the other day.
Yeah.

So this is what it looks
like, just very subtle.

You can make it as loose
in the back as you want.

OK, so if you have any
loose pieces coming out,
that's no problem.
Just stick a bobby pin in.
It'll fix it right up.

So this is the perfect
hairdo for a last minute,
"Oh, no, I woke up late!"

Or, "I have to
run out the door."

Or how about Black Friday
shopping this week?

So when you're
getting up at 4:00 AM,

or you're not going
to bed at all,
here's a good hairdo for you.

So have a great
holiday, you guys.

Don't forget to check out
the giveaway, especially
the awesome T-shirts.
And we will see you guys later.

Oh, it's all linked below, all
below, in the description box.
See you guys.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
OK.

And you can see, the bigger that
they are, the looser the curl
is.

So it's all in just
what your preference is.

We're getting ready to
start our trick-or-treating.
We have what?
-Cave woman.
MINDY: Cave woman.
What are you?
-Fairy.
MINDY: An autumn fairy?
Or a spring fairy?
-No, I'm an animal fairy.
MINDY: An animal fairy?
What kind of animal fairy?
-Uh, I can't remember.
-Hoomaha.
MINDY: Hoomaha.
-Yeah.
Hoomaha.
-Nice.
Special K is an Hoomaha.
-Yeah, I'm Hoomaha.

MINDY: You're a Native
American princess?
-Yes, whatever.
-She's an Egyptian.
-No, I'm not.
MINDY: An Egyptian?
SPECIAL K: I'm not an Egyptian.
-The wings.

MINDY: Oh, lookie who
we have over here.
Who are you?
Hi.

Are you our little
fluffy peacock?
GIRL: No.
GIRL: Yeah!
MINDY: Look at her face.
No?
Stand-- are you standing?
-No!
MINDY: OK.

I'm going to show you like her
whole costume from the side,

so you can see
how fluffy she is.
[LAUGHTER]
No, no.
Stay there.
And she's just turning.
There.
Look at how fluffy she is.
Oh.
Oh!
There she goes!
[LAUGHTER]
Hey!
Little fluffy peacock!
-Peacock.
MINDY: Oh, who do we have here?
-Zorro.
MINDY: Zorro.
Where's your hat?
MINDY: Oh, there it is.

Ooh, don't hit me
with that sword.
Who did a miss?
-Cat.
MINDY: I'm missing somebody.
Oh, yes, our kitty.
Meow.
-Rowr.
MINDY: Meow.
Look at those eyes.
Oooh.
GIRL: Is she getting a--

MINDY: Oh, and look
who got braces.
Oh, yes, and we forgot.
Da-da-da-nah!
We have Captain Jack over here.
-Yep.
I seem to have lost my ship.

Maybe you've heard of
it, "The Black Pearl."
MINDY: Maybe.
Where's your compass?

You need a cool compass
to help identify
where "The Black Pearl" is.
-I have a sword.
MINDY: OK, say bye.
Everyone say trick or treat!
ALL: Trick or treat.
-Say, Happy Halloween!
AL: Happy Halloween!
